{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "AIDLC Phase Guard",
  "description": "Before writing AIDLC output files, verify prerequisite phase outputs exist. Supports microservices pattern (domain-design-*.md).",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "preToolUse",
    "toolTypes": ["write"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check the file path about to be written.\n\nSKIP ENTIRELY (do nothing, proceed silently) if path contains ANY of:\n- .kiro/\n- .claude/skills/\n- .memory/\n- planning/decisions/\n- planning/plans/\n- audit.md\n- PROGRESS.md\n- qa-task-progress.md\n- dev-task-progress.md\n\nONLY check prerequisites if path contains outputs/ AND matches one of these output types:\n- user-stories.md → no prerequisite (first output)\n- domain-decomposition.md → requires: user-stories.md\n- domain-design*.md → requires: domain-decomposition.md\n- logical-design*.md → requires: domain-design*.md (any file matching pattern)\n- implementation-plan.md → requires: logical-design*.md\n- *.spec.ts or *.robot → requires: implementation-plan.md\n\nFor microservices: glob pattern — domain-design*.md matches domain-design-booking.md etc.\n\nIf prerequisite missing → STOP and tell user which file is needed first.\nIf prerequisite exists OR path not in outputs/ → proceed silently."
  }
}
